I don&#39;t think you should worry for with vanilla JS DOM manipulation in such cases, but if you want to make it react-ish you can use [Context][1].

First define your context:

    const CircleContext = React.createContext();

then wrap your app (or part of app where circles will be used) with `CircleContext.Provider` and set it&#39;s value to desired callback:

